<!--1 line-->

The RVM segment loader provides a mechanism that allows a load map to
be created for the mapped regions of a segment.  Regions can be mapped
to space allocated by RVM or to specific virtual memory addresses in a
single library call.  The segment loader is used by the RDS allocator
to automate the loading of the recoverable heap.

Detailed documentation of the library will be
included in a later version of this document.
For an indication of the functionality of the segment loader, its
header file is 
included in <ref id="RVMheaders" name="XXX"> on p. @PageRef(rvmsegh).


